# MDS Progress Bar Token Usage

## Critical Rule

**Always use MDS progress bar-specific tokens** (`--mds-progress-bar-*`) when styling progress bars. Never use generic tokens or hard-coded values.

## Available MDS Progress Bar Tokens

Reference: `/src/styles/mds/progress-bar.tokens.css`

### Height Tokens
```css
--mds-progress-bar-height-2px: 2px;
--mds-progress-bar-height-4px: 4px;
--mds-progress-bar-height-8px: 8px;
```

### Color Tokens
```css
--mds-progress-bar-track: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
--mds-progress-bar-fill: var(--mds-color-electric-blue-500);
--mds-progress-bar-text: var(--mds-color-text-default);
--mds-progress-bar-text-muted: var(--mds-color-text-subtle);
```

### Spacing Tokens
```css
--mds-progress-bar-gap: 8px;
```

## Critical: No Border Radius

**Progress bars have no border-radius token** - they should be flat/square, not rounded.

## Examples

### ✅ GOOD - Using MDS Progress Bar Tokens

```css
.progress-bar {
  width: 100%;
  height: var(--mds-progress-bar-height-4px);
  background-color: var(--mds-progress-bar-track);
  overflow: hidden;
  /* NO border-radius */
}

.progress-fill {
  height: 100%;
  background-color: var(--mds-progress-bar-fill);
  transition: width 0.3s ease;
}
```

```css
/* Different sizes */
.progress-bar--small {
  height: var(--mds-progress-bar-height-2px);
}

.progress-bar--medium {
  height: var(--mds-progress-bar-height-4px);
}

.progress-bar--large {
  height: var(--mds-progress-bar-height-8px);
}
```

### ❌ BAD - Using Generic Tokens or Hard-Coded Values

```css
.progress-bar {
  height: 6px; /* Wrong - use token */
  background-color: var(--mds-color-grey-200); /* Wrong - use --mds-progress-bar-track */
  border-radius: 3px; /* Wrong - no border radius on progress bars */
}

.progress-fill {
  background-color: var(--mds-color-electric-blue-500); /* Wrong - use --mds-progress-bar-fill */
}
```

```css
.progress-bar {
  background: #e5e5e5; /* Wrong - hard-coded color */
  border-radius: 4px; /* Wrong - no border radius */
}
```

