## Why This Matters

1. **Design Consistency**: Progress bars look the same across the entire application
2. **Theme Support**: Dark theme variants work automatically with MDS tokens
3. **Maintainability**: Changes to progress bar styles happen in one place (tokens file)
4. **Future-Proofing**: When MDS updates, progress bars update automatically
5. **No Rounded Corners**: MDS progress bars are flat by design - no border-radius token exists

## Verification Checklist

When creating or reviewing progress bar components, ensure:

- [ ] Height uses `--mds-progress-bar-height-*` tokens
- [ ] Track color uses `--mds-progress-bar-track`
- [ ] Fill color uses `--mds-progress-bar-fill`
- [ ] Label colors use `--mds-progress-bar-text` or `--mds-progress-bar-text-muted`
- [ ] Spacing uses `--mds-progress-bar-gap`
- [ ] NO `border-radius` property exists
- [ ] No hard-coded colors or dimensions
- [ ] No generic color tokens where specific progress bar tokens exist
